reviewText: This is a must have for any horse lover.  This is a Christmas gift for my 7 year old granddaughter.  She loves horses.
We bought this for the grandkids a thousand miles away and they called and said they loved it. My babies would never lie to grandma & grandpa pa, so based on that we highly recommend it.
When i got this saddle club and got ready to watch it,  realized the disc had a crack right down the middle! completely cut in half. I am very disappointed.

I have been a fan of the SADDLE CLUB for a very long time now having read all the books including pine hollow and i think its about time that this show was brought to the UK.It would seem that all the videos and records are only available outside the UK is it not about time that we were given an equal chance to get the products advertised at a fair price.
I ordered this DVD 4 pack for my Granddaughter when she was here on vacation. We watched it together.  A great DVD.

If you are looking for a good set for a horse-loving girl, these are your movies.  They are not going to win an Oscar, but they are decent entertainment for younger girls.  I bought these originally as a gift for someone else, but my younger daughter commandeered them.  Cheap enough that you can buy two.

This is billed as a "movie" four pack but there is not a "movie" at all.  Each "movie" is just several of the television show episodes played without interruption.  If you own the television series DO NOT buy this!  My daughter loves The Saddle Club and was very disappointed that this was nothing new, literally.  I was also not happy to spend money, however little, on something we already owned.

I bought this for my eight year old. The plot line is awful. I certainly wasn't expecting the foreign accents. When the kids broke out tarot cards I threw it away. I want my movies to send a good message and teach good lessons to my child as I watch it with her.  I was looking for a good kids movie involving horses that wasn't super cheesy. I am glad I bought the movie misty as well. That's a classic and as old as it is she still enjoyed it very much. I would give this a negative and it's not true to the book series.
